In the heady of 2002/2003, smartphones gained pace (thoguh Apple strangely reticent at this point about entering mobile market). Nokia and Ericsson was leading the early way with two early models, that formed basis of acceptance testing for MMS and mobile video streaming (in it's infancy). Many klate nights at the data centre near park royal, working with Nokia to test latest releases. We were in data centre to be close to the MMS and streaming servers.